  "prompt": "If I have someone blocked on Instagram, and view their story, can they see I viewed it?",
  "response": "If you have someone blocked on Instagram, you typically cannot view their story. Blocking someone restricts both accounts from interacting with each other, which includes viewing content like stories. However, if you unblock the person and then view their story, they will be able to see that you viewed it, just like any other viewer. Remember, Instagram's features and policies can change, so it's always a good idea to check for the latest updates directly from Instagram's help resources.",
